Block Element Modifier


    - A style for writing HTML/CSS to help developers stay organized 

    - BEM stands for Block Element Modifier

        - Block
            - the standalone entity that is meaningful on its own 
        
        - Element
            - a part of a block that has no standalone meaning, and is semantically tied to its block
        
        - Modifier
            - a flag on a block or element, used to change appearance or behavior 


    - General Syntax
        - Block     : class = "block"
        - Element   : class = "block__element"
        - Modifier  : class = "block--modifier"